 key aspects of Demy's cinema, including his associations with the New Wave, his unique approach to musicals, his adaptations of fairytales, his representations of gender and sexuality and his legacy as an iconic director for generations of audiences and filmmakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszFrance. 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Individual Director (see also BIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Entertainment & Performing Arts).2bisacsh  aDemy's cinema.  aDemy's musicals.  aFrench New Wave.  aFrench films.  aFrench popular imaginary.  aHollywood staple.  aJacques Demy.  aWestern societies.  aaffect.  afilmography.  afree will.  agender.  aiconic director.  aphilosophical reflections.  aposthumous myth.  arelations.  asexuality.  asubjectivity.  asugary coating.1 aWaldron, Darren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611135740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526111357423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526111357/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles